## Feature 1: PDF Export (Quick Win #4)

### Testing Results

**File Tested:** `src/services/notePdfExport.ts` (158 lines)
**Test Cases:** 9 total
**Passing:** 9/9 ✅ (after fixes)

| Test Case | Status | Notes |
|-----------|--------|-------|
| Export note with long title (>50 chars) | ✅ PASS | Filename truncation works (line 156) |
| Export note with special chars in title | ⚠️ FIXED | Regex too aggressive → Fixed (line 153) |
| Export empty note | ✅ PASS | Shows "(No content)" (lines 95-98) |
| Export note with 100+ paragraphs | ✅ PASS | Pagination logic works (lines 34-39) |
| Export note with tags | ✅ PASS | Tags appear in PDF header (lines 59-64) |
| Export from dark mode | ✅ PASS | PDF always black/white (line 76) |
| Click PDF button rapidly | ⚠️ FIXED | Added loading state to prevent spam |
| Export note with very long paragraph | ✅ PASS | `splitTextToSize()` wraps text (line 84) |
| Date serialization handling | ✅ PASS | Store converts string→Date (useNotesStore.ts:568-575) |

### Issues Found & Fixed

#### Issue 1: Overly Aggressive Filename Sanitization (MEDIUM)
**Problem:** Regex `/[^a-zA-Z0-9\s-]/g` removed ALL special characters including apostrophes, periods, quotes.

**Example:**
- Input: "Bob's Notes v2.0"
- Old output: `bobs-notes-v20-2025-11-18.pdf`
- New output: `bob's-notes-v2.0-2025-11-18.pdf` ✅

**Fix:** Modified regex to only remove filesystem-unsafe characters:
```typescript
// src/services/notePdfExport.ts:153
.replace(/[<>:"/\\|?*]/g, '') // Only remove chars that break filesystems
```

#### Issue 2: No Loading State (LOW)
**Problem:** PDF export button had no visual feedback during 1-2 second export (lazy load + generation time).

**User Impact:** Uncertainty if export is working, especially for large notes.

**Fix:** Added loading state to export button:
```typescript
// src/pages/Notes.tsx:415-432
const [isExporting, setIsExporting] = useState(false);

const handlePDFExport = async (e: React.MouseEvent) => {
  e.stopPropagation();
  setIsExporting(true);
  try {
    await exportNoteToPDF(note, onSuccess);
  } finally {
    setIsExporting(false);
  }
};

// Button shows ⏳ while exporting, 📄 when idle
{isExporting ? '⏳' : '📄'}
```

#### Issue 3: No Success Notification (LOW)
**Problem:** User got no confirmation that export succeeded (only console.log).

**User Impact:** Uncertainty if export worked, especially if download doesn't immediately show.

**Fix:** Added success notification (3-second green toast):
```typescript
// src/pages/Notes.tsx:483-487
{exportSuccess && (
  <div className="absolute -top-8 left-0 right-0 bg-green-500 text-white text-xs py-1 px-2 rounded shadow-lg z-10 text-center">
    ✓ Exported: {exportSuccess}
  </div>
)}
```

### Files Modified

1. **src/services/notePdfExport.ts** (3 changes):
   - Lines 15-18: Added `onSuccess` callback parameter
   - Line 153: Fixed filename sanitization regex
   - Lines 127-129: Call success callback after export

2. **src/pages/Notes.tsx** (3 changes):
   - Lines 415-432: Added `handlePDFExport` with loading state
   - Lines 483-487: Added success notification toast
   - Lines 502-508: Updated button to use loading state

